5wve K 258 M 115

A redox-regulated disulphide may form between two units of Apoptotic protease-activating factor 1 at these cysteines. However, the redox score of this cysteine pair is lower than any known redox-active disulphide.

Apoptotic protease-activating factor 1

5juy E 675 E 749

A redox-regulated disulphide may form within Apoptotic protease-activating factor 1 at these cysteines. However, the redox score of this cysteine pair is lower than any known redox-active disulphide.
